name: treatment of residues, MSWI-WWT, WW, average, residual material landfill | residues, MSWI-WWT, WW, average | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/26579/documentation

The process represents the treatment of a waste (residues) that is exclusively produced from another waste treatment. Residues are generated in the municipal solid waste incineration (MSWI) of sewage sludge (with 70% water) that in turn is generated from wastewater treatment (WWT) of 'wastewater, average'. Recommended use of this dataset: to be used within the specific chain of treatments for 'wastewater, average'. Share of biogenic carbon in the sludge: 97.491%.

The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included.

The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfarming process are released to the environment (air, water and soil). The activity is considering local fate of emissions and the initial specific wastewater composition (generating the sewage sludge).
category: E:Water supply; sewerage, waste management and remediation activities/38:Waste collection, treatment and disposal activities; materials recovery/382:Waste treatment and disposal/3822:Treatment and disposal of hazardous waste

processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Modelling parameters affecting the treatment technology are not specific to this geography.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Residual material landfill for polluted, inorganic waste with base seal and leachate collection system. Recultivation after closure.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Modelling parameters are based on an average residual material landfill in Switzerland.
